# $Id: README,v 1.1 2008/04/30 22:59:42 jwz Exp $

Snark - A series of scripts to run a Translux Datawall from the serial
or ethernet port for a nightclub.

Requirements:

- SnarkAPI - Open Source Datawall API. 
- Translux Datawall (duh.)
- A web server (apache!)
- Serial interface to the datawall (see DATAWALL for more info)
   - We're using a Lantronix UDS-10 Ethernet to Serial adapter 
- Perl 5

...and A few PERL Modules:

Config::INI::Simple - Manages the "config" file, snark.ini, which is
actually the main message and control database. 
Text::Template - To provide for seperation of code and layout for the HTML pages
HTML::TagFilter - To filter out html from posts.
Text::Wrap - To wrap text when sending it to the sign.
Net::SMTP - For the SMTP Interface
HTML::Parser
MIME::Parser - Parse and process incoming messages 
Getopt::Long - Processes options

Optional Plugins:

Geo::WeatherNWS - if you want the weather.
XML::Parser::Lite - to parse XML 
XML::RSS::Parser::Lite - to parse RSS

